                  </persName>
             sworn.</p>
               <p>I am the keeper of the Bridewell at Reading. On Friday morning was se'nnight, I was sent for by a gentleman to take charge of the prisoner, whom he had stopped on suspicion of his having stolen some plate. I found the plate in the landlord's hand, the prisoner threatened to punish the people that stopped him; and said, he was sent by his mistress with the plate to Bath, and had the key of the plate chest.</p>
               <p>[A silver steak-dish and cover produced and deposed to.]</p>
               <p>
            
